# Creating a New Presentation

## Overview

This project supports two types of presentations:

1. **Slide-based** (like `use-effect`) - Sequential slides with arrow key navigation
2. **Route-based** (like `css`) - Each section is a separate route with a lobby page

## Directory Structure

```
src/lectures/<lecture-name>/
├── index.tsx           # Main entry point
├── examples/           # Code examples (optional)
├── components/         # Reusable components (optional)
└── style.css           # Custom styles (optional)
```

## Pattern 1: Slide-Based Presentation

Best for: Linear presentations with sequential content

### Entry Point (`index.tsx`)

```tsx
import { Typography, Stack, Divider } from "@mui/joy";
import Slide from "../../common/slide";
import { Presentation } from "../../presentation-framework";
import Code from "../../presentation-framework/code";
import { CodeWithRender } from "../../common/code-with-render";

const slides = [
  () => (
    <Slide alignItems="center" justifyContent="center" textAlign="center">
      <Typography level="h1" sx={{ fontSize: "7rem" }}>
        Title Slide
      </Typography>
    </Slide>
  ),
  () => (
    <Slide gap={4}>
      <Typography level="h1">Content Slide</Typography>
      {/* slide content */}
    </Slide>
  ),
];

export default function LectureName() {
  return <Presentation slides={slides} />;
}
```

### Key Components

- `<Slide>` - Wrapper component (accepts all MUI Joy Stack props)
- `<Presentation slides={slides}>` - Handles navigation with arrow keys
- `<Code>{codeString}</Code>` - Syntax highlighted code block
- `<CodeWithRender code={raw} component={<Component />}>` - Toggle code view with live render

### Importing Raw Code

```tsx
import ExampleComponent from "./examples/example.tsx";
import exampleCode from "./examples/example.tsx?raw";

// Use in slide
<CodeWithRender code={exampleCode} component={<ExampleComponent />} />;
```

## Pattern 2: Route-Based Presentation

Best for: Topic collections with individual sections

### Entry Point (`<name>.tsx`)

```tsx
import { NavLink, useRoutes } from "react-router-dom";
import Lobby from "./lobby";
import SectionOne from "./section-one";

export default function LectureName() {
  const sections = [
    {
      path: "section-one",
      title: "Section One",
      element: <SectionOne />,
    },
  ];

  sections.unshift({
    index: true,
    title: "Lecture Name",
    element: <Lobby sections={sections} />,
  });

  const router = useRoutes(sections);

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-5 p-8 h-full">
      <div className="flex flex-row gap-2 items-end">
        <NavLink to="/lecture-name" className="text-5xl font-bold leading-none">
          Lecture Name
        </NavLink>
        <p className="text-xl">Subtitle</p>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <div className="transition-all duration-300">{router}</div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Lobby Component

```tsx
import { NavLink } from "react-router-dom";

export default function Lobby({ sections }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-center">
      <ul className="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
        {sections
          .filter((s) => !s.index && s.path)
          .map((section) => (
            <li key={section.path}>
              <NavLink
                className="bg-blue-500 p-2 rounded-md"
                to={`/lecture-name/${section.path}`}
              >
                {section.title}
              </NavLink>
            </li>
          ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Registering the Presentation

### 1. Add route in `src/main.tsx`

```tsx
import LectureName from "./lectures/<lecture-name>/index.tsx";

// In router children array:
{
  path: "lecture-name", // or "lecture-name/*" for route-based
  element: <LectureName />,
},
```

### 2. Add button in `src/App.tsx`

```tsx
<Button onClick={() => navigate("/lecture-name")}>Lecture Name</Button>
```

## Available UI Components

### From MUI Joy

- `Typography` - Text with levels (h1, h2, h3, body-lg, body-md, body-sm)
- `Stack` - Flexbox container
- `Divider` - Horizontal/vertical divider
- `Card` - Content card
- `List`, `ListItem` - List components
- `Button`, `IconButton` - Buttons

### From Presentation Framework

- `Code` - Syntax highlighted code (pass string as children)
- `Presentation` - Slide deck wrapper with navigation

### From Common

- `Slide` - Full-height slide wrapper (extends MUI Stack)
- `CodeWithRender` - Code toggle with live component preview

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS classes for layout
- Use MUI Joy `sx` prop for component-specific styles
- Dark theme is applied by default via `ThemeProvider`

## Tips

- Slides are React functional components (FC[])
- Navigation: Arrow keys (left/right) or bottom buttons
- URL tracks slide index via `?s=` query param
- Use `level` prop on Typography for semantic headings
- Import code files with `?raw` suffix for display
